<subsection xml:id="subsec-representing-length-to-a-given-scale">
    <title>Representing length to a given scale</title>
    <p>
        Representing length to a given scale involves creating a proportional representation of real-world measurements, typically in drawings, maps, or models.
    </p>
    <p>
        A scale is a ratio that compares the dimensions of a representation (like a drawing) to the corresponding dimensions of the actual object. It indicates how much smaller or larger the representation is compared to reality.
    </p>
    <activity>
        <p>
            Work in groups
        </p>
        <p>
            The teacher provided the learners with a textbook, a ruler, and an exercise book for the activity.
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Individually, draw the textbook accurately in your exercise book.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        How different is the length of your drawing from the actual length of the textbook?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Measure the actual length of the textbook and the length of your drawing in centimetres.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Share your work with the other groups and compare results.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>
